item.title: CVE-2020-29492|2024-08-04T16:55:09.896Z -- dell -- wyse%20proprietary%20os%20%28thinos%29
item.description: Dell Wyse ThinOS 8.6 and prior versions contain an insecure default configuration vulnerability. A remote unauthenticated attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability to access the writable file and manipulate the configuration of any target specific station.

item.title: CVE-2020-29491|2024-08-04T16:55:10.260Z -- dell -- wyse%20proprietary%20os%20%28thinos%29
item.description: Dell Wyse ThinOS 8.6 and prior versions contain an insecure default configuration vulnerability. A remote unauthenticated attacker could potentially exploit this vulnerability to gain access to the sensitive information on the local network, leading to the potential compromise of impacted thin clients.
